    "media:imagetext": "THE NEW CLIPPER AMERICA\nNO TRAFFIC JAM IN THE GALLEY\nEven with a large galley, the serving oi 61\npersons might have created a sèrious traffic jam but\nfor the development of the serving door pictured\nabove. Closed it does not suggest the presence of\nany such mundane equipment as a house-keeping\nkitchen. For the few minutes required for the\nserving of meals, the five louvres are opened and\ntrays passed back and forth. The flight chef inside\ndevotes his full attention to the cooking and\npreparation of meals. The two stewardesses do the\nserving. At right is the stewardess'\nstation. Call\nsignals from passengers appear as lights above the\nstewardess' head.\nPAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS\n135 East 42nd Street\nNer Xy111 647100\nFor Immediate Release",
